 ("nm1131087", null, null, null, null, null, null, "6' (1.83 m)", "Anthony Welch is an American Actor, Writer, Producer, born and raised in NYC. Theater trained at The Lee Strasberg Theater Institute in New York City, Anthony has appeared in numerous theater and film productions. Anthony lived in Los Angeles from 1990-1995, where he appeared in The Jones Boy at The Third Street Theater, for which he won a L.A. Drama-Logue Critics Award for Best Ensemble Performance as The Trick. Anthony also appeared in the Cult Film Classic, \"Life Among The Cannibals\", where he played Detective Charlie alongside Kieran Mulroney. Anthony left the industry for 17 years to have and raise a family, which accounts for the gap in his work. However, Anthony has returned to an industry he has always loved and is currently working on a project he created, wrote, Executive Produced and Co-Stars in titled \"Street Smart\", where he plays retired NYPD Detective Joey McGloin. Anthony was also cast in the Martin Scorsese film, The Irishman, as a Prison Guard that personally escorts Jimmy Hoffa, (Played by Al Pacino) out of the prison upon his release. The Irishman is scheduled to be released in 2019. Anthony currently resides in NYC.", null, null, "Anthony", null, "Welch", null, null, "Anthony Welch"),
 ("nm4893606", null, null, null, null, null, null, "5' 7\" (1.7 m)", "Kelly P. Williams an American actress known for her onscreen wit and intense presence. She's graced the stage in numerous theatrical productions, concert dance companies and theme parks. Kelly holds a Bachelors in Fine Arts from Florida State University, as well as an Associates in Arts from Florida School of the Performing Arts, and has her own successful photography business and production company.", null, null, "Kelly", "P.", "Williams", null, null, "Kelly P. Williams"),
 ("nm2524437", null, null, null, null, null, null, null, "A native of Ft. Lauderdale, Florida, this Southern Belle's roots were firmly planted in the world of dance and performing on stage before her desire to move into film acting following the birth of her two children. Landing several award winning lead roles in community theater and student films, she decided to hit the other side of the camera enrolling at the Miami film school in 2010. Already having completed a B.S degree in Communications from Kennesaw State University in 1997, Carole said \"Education is a lifelong process and it is never too late to go back to school.\"A former NFL Pro Bowl cheerleader for the Atlanta Falcons, the blond hair, blue eyed Wood signed on as Cheerleading Coordinator for the Tampa Bay Buccaneers and helped the team earn top honors as Best NFL Cheer Squad in 1998 from Pro Football Weekly magazine. It was within the 12 years working in the NFL where Carole got her first real taste at stardom working alongside music giants Shania Twain, MC Hammer, Toby Keith, Travis Tritt, Santana and Shaggy during team choreography sessions and performances.Carole recently wrote, starred in and produced \"Krissy Belle,\" described as a sitcom style script edited in the form of a feature film. Krissy Belle premiered during the Fort Lauderdale Film Festival in 2013. \"Krissy Belle\" is a modern comedy appealing to the English/Spanish Bilingual community.Carole is married with two children.", null, null, "Carole", null, "Wood", null, null, "Carole Wood"),
 ("nm6368573", null, null, null, null, null, null, null, "Renee Wood was born in New York. Her career began when she started doing theatre in New York. Her theatrical debut performance in the play \"The Christmas Carol\" earned her rave reviews by The New York Times and critiques said, \"Renee Wood, articulated her lines with the clarity of Jane Fonda.\" She has studied acting at the renowned Lee Strasberg Theatre Institute in NYC. Renee has done theatre, films, and also has been a news correspondent/host for SI Cable and has hosted venues for philanthropic endeavors along with event for the Grammys. Renee Wood was awarded the \"20 under 40\" Leadership Award from The Staten Island Economic Development Corporation. This prestigious accolade is awarded to Staten Island's brightest young stars who work and/or live in the borough and are making a difference in their respective field.", null, null, "Renee", null, "Wood", null, null, "Renee Wood"),
