 ("nm7104742", null, null, null, null, null, null, null, "Michael DeBartolo graduated from Michigan State University and UCLA where he received Bachelor and Master of Science degrees in Mechanical Engineering, but also studied acting at both universities being accepted into the MPTV Program at UCLA. He studied acting under well-known actors/directors such as Ivan Curry, Jerome Guardino, Art Friedman, and George Peppard.While working as an engineer at Boeing in El Segundo, California, he starred in many plays and musicals all over Los Angeles including Hollywood. He also won featured roles in film and television. Films include The Blues Brothers (1980), The Patricia Neal Story (1981), Moving Violations (1985), Hail Caesar! (2016), How to be a Latin Lover (2017), City of Lies (2018) and Ford V. Ferrari (2019). TV Shows include Taxi (1981), The Bernie Mac Show (2005), CSI: New York (2005), Sons and Daughters (2006), Make It or Break It (2011), Vegas (2012), 90201 (2013), Dads (2013), Brooklyn Nine-Nine (2014), Mad Men (2014), State of Affairs (2015), Jane the Virgin (2015), Bosch (2016), Idiotsitter (2016), Heartbeat (2016), People Magazine Investigates (2016), Shameless (2017), and Corporate (2018).He also advanced to more memorable and starring roles in film and television. For instance, in films he played the Uncle of Frankie Valli (John Lloyd Young) in Jersey Boys (2014), Ron DeFeo Sr., the Amityville Horror Father, in The Conjuring 2: The Enfield Poltergeist (2016), and the St. Valentine's Day Massacre Undercover Policeman and Hitman for Al Capone (Milo Gibson) in Gangster Land (2017). In TV series he played Arman, the Tailor of Peter Schaefer (Luke Perry) in Windfall (2006), Bill Morrisey, the Unusual Suspect in Unusual Suspects (2006), Keith Dahl, the victim in It Takes a Killer (2016), the Theme Park Dad in If Theme Parks Were Honest - Honest Ads (2017), and the Italian Dad from Jersey Shores in Laff Mobb's Laff Tracks (2018). He also wrote, produced, and starr